main event: Reports of unidentified flying objects (UFOs) in the Houston, Texas area during August 1965.
interesting points: Sighting reports were clustered from August 11-31, 1965; The first reports followed radar sightings in early August; Witnesses described the objects as very bright with no visible means of propulsion; Multiple witnesses claimed to have seen the same object, noting it had bright, luminous features; No physical evidence or official conclusions were provided.
witness description: Civilians and military personnel reported sightings, noting the object's bright appearance and erratic movement.
